        <div n="807-002H" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">By <hi rend="underline">Dean</hi> Swift.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-1"> Wou'd you rise in the Church, be stupid and dull,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-2"> Be empty of Learning, of insolence full;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-3"> Tho^ lewd and immorral, be formal and grave,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-4"> In flatt'ring, an Artist; in fawning, a Slave.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-5"> No Merit, no Science, no Virtue i<subst reason="apparently overwriting"><add>s</add><del>n</del></subst> wanting.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-6"> In him, that's accomplish'd in cringing and Canting.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-7"> Be Studious to practise true meaness of Spirit:</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-8"> And who, but L<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Bolton was Mitred for Merit?</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-9"> Wou'd you wish to be wrap'd in a Rochet?──in short</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-807-002H-line-10"> Be as pox'd and prophane as fanatical H────807-002H   </l></lg></div>
